				<div>   </div>
			</div>				
	
	
	
	</td>
	
	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_762622">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_762622">Apparently, in addition to the +defense and rank 1 spell nerfs in 1.7, they stealth-nerfed Invulnerable Mail: <a href="http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.aspx?FN=wow-general&amp;T=4522354&amp;P=1" target="_blank">http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/th...&amp;T=4522354&amp;P=1</a>.  Gratz to everyone who farmed weeks on end for the materials or dropped 1200-1300 gold on this item.  It's now vendor trash.<br />
<br />
Anyone else feeling yet that it's a serious detriment to the game when Blizzard makes major nerfs like this EVERY PATCH?  A fundamental part of the MMORPG experience, particularly at the high end, is that you put in a lot of effort to reach character accomplishment milestones -- levels, gear sets, PvP ranks, whatever -- and then your character becomes stronger as a result that effort.  Your Amulet of Uberness off the Mega Raid Boss makes all those months of boring trash clear (or all the boring farming, all the boring tradeskill grinding, all the whatever) worth it.<br />
<br />
As it is now, though, it's hard to figure what to strive for, because who knows when it's going to be taken away.  Do I want to grind high-level instances for a month to get my set armor, when the next patch might say, "We think Valor had too much STA, so it's all been removed and replaced with +dodge"?  I guess I will as long as I want to play the game.  But MMORPGs are always about keeping that carrot out in front of the players, tantalizing them to continue playing... if there's a real chance the carrot will disappear when I get to it, will I still want it as much?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				WoW: <a href=http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?132163>Martar</a>, 54 human warrior, Windrunner<br />
EQ: <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=802010>Master Spiffe</a>, 65 wizard (retired), Mith Marr<br />
<br />
<font size="1"><i>All classes are overpowered, except the one I play.</i></font>
			</div>
