	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Niccolo</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Nerfs are an unfortunate reality of MMOs, which need them in order to keep the game competitive and ongoing, as well as to prevent players from actually feeling as if they have "beaten" the game.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Huh?  You keep people interested in the game by presenting *new* challenges, not increasing the difficulty of ones they've already completed.  It's, "Now that you've bested the dreaded dragon Onyxia, can you defeat Deathwing?", not "Now that you've bested Onyxia, we're going to change the encounter again to make it more difficult... can you defeat Onyxia 3.1?"  That's no kind of fun.<br />
<br />
I understand that nerfs are sometimes necessary to maintain game balance.  What I take issue with is the frequency and capriciousness with which Blizzard makes these sweeping nerfs.  Nerfing Rank 1 spells is a *big* change that vastly affects caster gameplay.  Was it really necessary?  Did anyone think it was overpowered?<br />
<br />
A nerf here, a nerf there, is unfortunate, but understandable.  A nerf everywhere, all the time, is highly disruptive and causes a lot of strife within the playerbase.  Do they just not care?  I'm not yet to the point where I'm apathetic to advancing my character because I expect a nerf to anything good, but I can see the game heading down that path, and it's not a good one for customer retention.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
